"{\"uid\": \"si.com-college-oklahoma-other-sooners-a-look-at-oklahoma-athletes-competing-in-paris-olympics-01j3zd36e8zc\", \"text\": \"In this story:  There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a pipeline from Norman to Paris.\\u00c2  Seven current or former Oklahoma athletes are competing at the 2024 Paris Olympic Games, which kicked off Friday with Opening Ceremonies. The games will conclude with Closing Ceremonies on Aug. 11.\\u00c2  Sooners competing in Paris includeAbraham Ancer(men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s golf),Emre Dodanli(men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s gymnastics),James Fraschilla(3x3 men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s basketball),Ralford Mullings(men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s track & field),Abi Olajuwon(women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s basketball),Ama Pipi(women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s track & field) andVernon Turner(men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s track & field). With the addition of seven new athletes, OU has now produced 89 Olympians. A former or current Sooner has competed in the last 22 Olympic Games.\\u00c2  Here\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a closer look at each Sooner competing in Paris.\\u00c2  At 33, this is Ancer\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s second time representing Mexico at the Olympics. He also competed at the Tokyo Olympics in 2021. Although born in McAllen, TX, Ancer spent time in Reynosa, Mexico while growing up and has dual citizenship.\\u00c2  After a one-year stint at Odessa College, Ancer transferred to OU, where he graduated in 2013. Ancer left Norman second all-time in scoring average in program history. He then started his professional career immediately and now competes on the LIV Golf Tour.\\u00c2  The men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s golf competition will start at 2 a.m. Thursday and wraps up with Round 4 on Sunday.\\u00c2  Dodanli became an Olympian before even concluding his collegiate career with OU. Just finishing his junior season, Dodanli will compete in men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s gymnastics for Turkey. This is the first time in its country\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s history that Turkey qualified a team in men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s gymnastics. Dodanli won gold in the all-around at the Turkish Artistic Gymnastics Championship earlier this summer.\\u00c2  Dodanli was the first Sooner to compete in Paris, with men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s gymnastics qualification on Saturday. The individual all-around final will be Wednesday. Event finals start Saturday.\\u00c2  Fraschilla will represent OU in a different way as an assistant coach on the USA Men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 3x3 Basketball National Team. He walked onto the Sooners\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 basketball team before graduating in 2015 and following in his father\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s footsteps as a coach.\\u00c2  This is only the second Olympics with 3x3 basketball, however, the U.S. did not qualify for the Tokyo Olympics. USA\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s first men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 3x3 game in an Olympics will be against Serbia at 3:35 p.m. Tuesday.\\u00c2  Mullings will compete in the discus throw for Jamaica. He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s originally from Kingston, Jamaica. Although a junior at OU, Mullings actually hasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t even competed for the Sooners yet after transferring from Arkansas and starting his career at Arizona State. He competed unattached this past season.\\u00c2  The discus throw competition will start on Aug. 5 with qualification.\\u00c2  Born in Houston but of Nigerian descent, the daughter of NBA legendHakeem \\\"The Dream\\\" Olajuwonis an assistant coach for Nigeria\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s basketball team. She was a McDonald\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s All-American before getting to OU in 2006. She averaged 10.6 points a game as a senior in 2009-10 before a brief WNBA career. She then got into coaching, currently serving as an assistant for the Connecticut Sun.\\u00c2  Nigeria plays France at 10:15 a.m. Thursday after beating Australia 75-62 early Monday morning.\\u00c2  Born in London, Pipi will compete in a pair of events for Great Britain, including the 400 meter and 4x400 relay, in her second Olympics at 28. Her team finished fifth in the 4x400 relay in Tokyo.\\u00c2  Pipi attended OU in 2015-18, becoming an All-American in 2018 and winning a Big 12 title in the 200 meter. She also holds the school record in the indoor 400-meter sprint.\\u00c2  Pipi will start with the 400 meter on Aug. 5.\\u00c2  Having just finished his OU career in 2023, Turner will represent the United States in high jump. He still holds the program record in the outdoor and indoor high jump. He was also an indoor NCAA champion in 2022. Turner is the only Oklahoman on this list, having attended Yukon High School. However, he was born in Kansas City, MO, so the state of Missouri gets to claim Turner as an Olympian.\\u00c2  The high jump competition will start with qualification on Aug. 7.  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations    \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC. - All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands. All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\"}"